{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:53:16.026Z",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Before transformers, "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "word embeddings",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " like Word2Vec and GloVe represented each word as a single static vector learned from co-occurrence statistics. These methods established the core idea that meaning lives in vector geometry — an idea carried forward into LLM token embeddings and dedicated retrieval encoders used by modern agents."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A word embedding assigns each word (or token) a dense vector such that words appearing in similar contexts have similar vectors. Word2Vec uses shallow neural networks (Skip-gram or CBOW) to predict context words. GloVe factorizes global co-occurrence statistics. Both produce static embeddings — one vector per word regardless of surrounding sentence context."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Static embeddings powered early semantic search, recommendation, and clustering systems. Understanding them clarifies why \"bank\" (river) and \"bank\" (finance) share one vector (a limitation), and why transformers replaced static embeddings with contextual representations. Agent developers still encounter static embeddings in legacy indexes and lightweight similarity tools."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Simple and fast",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — cheap to train and query on CPU"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Interpretable geometry",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — king - man + woman ≈ queen famously"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Good baseline retrieval",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — adequate for coarse semantic search"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Small footprint",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — megabyte-scale models for mobile or edge"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "One vector per word ignores context — \"bank\" gets a single blended meaning"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Out-of-vocabulary words require unknown-token handling or subword fallbacks"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Inferior to contextual embeddings on nuanced agent retrieval tasks"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Trained on static corpora — no instruction-following or reasoning capability"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How it works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Skip-gram trains a classifier to predict surrounding words given a center word. Weights from the hidden layer become embedding vectors."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from gensim.models import Word2Vec\n\nsentences = [\n    [\"agent\", \"calls\", \"tool\", \"to\", \"fetch\", \"weather\"],\n    [\"llm\", \"generates\", \"response\", \"after\", \"tool\", \"result\"],\n    [\"agent\", \"loops\", \"until\", \"task\", \"complete\"],\n]\n\nmodel = Word2Vec(sentences, vector_size=100, window=5, min_count=1, epochs=50)\nvector = model.wv[\"agent\"]\nsimilar = model.wv.most_similar(\"tool\", topn=3)\nprint(similar)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Modern agents prefer contextual encoders, but the similarity API pattern is identical:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity\nimport numpy as np\n\n# Static vectors (illustrative)\nv_agent = model.wv[\"agent\"].reshape(1, -1)\nv_robot = model.wv.get_vector(\"robot\", norm=True).reshape(1, -1) if \"robot\" in model.wv else v_agent\nscore = cosine_similarity(v_agent, v_robot)[0, 0]\nprint(f\"Similarity: {score:.3f}\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to use it"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Use static embeddings only for lightweight prototypes, educational examples, or legacy systems. Prefer sentence-transformer or API embedding models for production agent RAG. Study word embeddings to understand the foundation of all embedding-based retrieval."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Examples"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Word2Vec captures that \"agent\" and \"assistant\" are closer than \"agent\" and \"banana.\" It fails when \"python\" means the language versus the snake — context determines meaning, but static embeddings pick one average."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Real-world example"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A 2019 internal search tool indexed support tickets with GloVe 300-d vectors. Migrating to a sentence-transformer encoder improved recall@5 from 58% to 79% on paraphrased queries — the legacy system treated each word independently; the new system encodes full sentence context."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Deploying Word2Vec for production agent RAG in 2025+ without benchmarking against contextual encoders"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Averaging word vectors for sentence meaning without understanding information loss"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Ignoring OOV handling for domain jargon and product names"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use static embeddings for learning and baselines, not primary agent retrieval"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "When migrating legacy systems, re-embed documents with contextual models"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Understand cosine similarity and vector normalization regardless of embedding type"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Comparison with alternatives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Static word embeddings: one vector per word, fast, context-blind. Contextual transformer embeddings: different vector for the same word in different sentences — essential for accurate agent retrieval. LLM token embeddings are contextual when extracted from hidden states but static at the input embedding layer."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mental model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Static word embeddings assign each word a fixed seat in a semantic room. Contextual embeddings give each word a different seat depending on who else is in the conversation."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Word2Vec and GloVe pioneered dense semantic vectors from co-occurrence patterns"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Static embeddings have one vector per word — no context sensitivity"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Modern agents use contextual embedding models for retrieval"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Understanding static embeddings clarifies the evolution to transformer representations"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
